SIMPLE: moony
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Moony
<hw>Moon"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or
pertaining to the moon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Soft and pale as the <qex>moony</qex> beam.</q> <rj><qau>J. R.
Drake.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Furnished with a moon; bearing a crescent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>But soon the miscreant <qex>moony</qex> host⟦br⟧
Before the victor cross shall fly.</q> <rj><qau>Fenton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Silly; weakly sentimental.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark> <rj><au>G. Eliot.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Moony</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Moony
<hw>Moon"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>A follower of the
<person>Rev. Sun Myun <etsep>Moon</etsep></person>; a member of the
<membof>Unification Church</membof>; -- often considered
disparaging.</def> <altsp>[Also spelled <asp>Moonie</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Moor</ent>⟦br⟧
